					<div class="post" id="post-753">
			<div class="post-content-wp">
					<h2 class="posttitle"><a href="http://pettradeworld.com/2009/11/a-unique-staff-training-opportunity/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to A Unique Staff Training Opportunity">A Unique Staff Training Opportunity</a></h2>
					<p class="date"><span class="byline">Nov 29 2009 in <a href="http://pettradeworld.com/category/blog/" title="View all posts in News" rel="category tag">News</a> <em>by <a href="http://naidre" title="Visit naidre&#8217;s website" rel="external">naidre</a></em></span></p>
						<div class="entry">
								
							<p><strong>SafePets UK, founded by Debbie Connolly, has introduced a series of in store training sessions for pet shop staff.  </strong></p>
<p>Many pet owners use their local pet shops as a source of advice.  This advice can often be very good, but sometimes it isn’t and could be potentially dangerous. The <strong>SafePets UK</strong> training courses are designed to enable your staff to advise and help your customers safely. It is NOT a replacement for professional behaviour advice and assessments nor is it going to give staff the idea they are behaviourists.  It will pull together the mix of good, bad and old wives tales out there and offer something more uniform and professional that will add value to your business.</p>
<p>There are three levels of training &#8211; Bronze, Silver and Gold, which give everyone a chance to develop. The courses cover topics such as:<br />
•	Does food affect behaviour?<br />
•	What&#8217;s the best housetraining route?<br />
•	Is a headcollar or harness better?<br />
•	What&#8217;s the best toy to stop chewing?<br />
•	Can I stop spraying?<br />
•	What&#8217;s the difference in anti bark collars?<br />
In addition, some bespoke tailoring can be built into the courses around your best selling products or to promote poor selling lines.</p>
<p>Staff passing the course will each receive a certificate of their success and will be expected to sign and adhere to a Code of Conduct.</p>
<p><strong>Debbie Connolly</strong> is a well known animal behaviourist.  She is an Associate Member of the British Institute of Professional Dog Trainers and is the behaviour consultant for Zep the Dep Rottweiler Rescue and Bengal Cat Rescue. Training will therefore focus on dogs and cats and some livestock where appropriate.</p>
<p><strong>Course Prices: </strong><br />
A day in store is £200 for the first staff member, £100 each for any additional staff trained on the same day.</p>
<p>A residential option is available which costs £250 for a day of training and an overnight stay.  For any additional member of staff added to the same course, the cost would be £100 each. </p>
<p>You will be asked to carry promotional literature in store to support the training courses and help your customers understand what you are offering. </p>
<p>You will need the permission of your store owner or manager if you wish to book a place on a course. For more details on the courses available telephone <strong>08712 317415</strong>, email <strong><a href="mailto:training@safepets.co.uk">training@safepets.co.uk</a> </strong> or visit <strong><a href="http://www.safepets.co.uk">www.safepets.co.uk</a></strong></p>
						</div>
