					<div class="post" id="post-714">
			<div class="post-content-wp">
					<h2 class="posttitle"><a href="http://pettradeworld.com/2009/06/publicity-%e2%80%93-the-ptw-editor-has-an-opinion/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Publicity – The PTW editor has an opinion.">Publicity – The PTW editor has an opinion.</a></h2>
					<p class="date"><span class="byline">Jun 1 2009 in <a href="http://pettradeworld.com/category/blog/" title="View all posts in News" rel="category tag">News</a> <em>by <a href="http://naidre" title="Visit naidre&#8217;s website" rel="external">naidre</a></em></span></p>
						<div class="entry">
								
							<p>Now there’s a funny thing. Wouldn’t you just think that all companies would be falling over themselves for FREE publicity? Wrong. It never ceases to amaze us here at Pet Trade World, the number of companies who are conveniently unable to speak to a member of our editorial team! Let’s be honest here, whether we’re ringing for editorial help and advice or &#8211; heaven forbid &#8211; advertising, we are still offering to help promote a company in some way.</p>
<p>Remember that old adage &#8211; ALL publicity is good publicity? Perhaps some companies should bear it in mind when one of their products has been mentioned in a way they wouldn’t have chosen themselves, despite our numerous unanswered requests to them prior to publication!</p>
<p>And speaking of advertising &#8211; companies should also be aware that when they are placing their hard-earned advertising budget into the hands of large Advertising Agencies &#8211; that they are not necessarily paying commission for their expertise. At times, it is highly unlikely that a ‘Planner’ will be aware of ALL titles in the market, unless the titles have been around for at least 4 years and/or have an ABC (meaning that they are members of the Audit Bureau of Circulation). Many smaller ‘niche’ titles will probably never bother.  This invariably means that a ‘Planner’ may not actually be planning the most effective campaign at all. </p>
<p>If anyone is unsure about how to plan a campaign then anyone here will be pleased to help. After all, there is over 40 years publishing experience in our Publisher and Editor alone&#8230;&#8230;..that’s probably more than some agency planning departments employing 10 times that many! </p>
						</div>
																						<p class="postmetadata"><span class="tags"></span></p>
			</div>
		</div>
					<div class="post" id="post-688">
			<div class="post-content-wp">
					<h2 class="posttitle"><a href="http://pettradeworld.com/2009/02/pet-trade-world-distribution-leads-the-way/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to PET TRADE WORLD DISTRIBUTION LEADS THE WAY">PET TRADE WORLD DISTRIBUTION LEADS THE WAY</a></h2>
					<p class="date"><span class="byline">Feb 11 2009 in <a href="http://pettradeworld.com/category/blog/" title="View all posts in News" rel="category tag">News</a> <em>by <a href="http://naidre" title="Visit naidre&#8217;s website" rel="external">naidre</a></em></span></p>
						<div class="entry">
								
							<p>Only 18 months after its launch, Pet Trade World has announced a record distribution of 12,000 copies a month.</p>
<p>Pet Trade World was already the only digital magazine in the international pet trade and the new circulation increase now makes it the highest circulating title as well.</p>
<p>The magazines 12,000 circulation includes retailers, manufacturers, vets, kennels and catteries, garden centres, equine and aquatic related outlets and pet related organisations throughout the UK and the rest of the world. New requests for subscriptions continue to be received each month so the circulation is likely to continue growing for the foreseeable future.</p>
<p>The staff behind the digital magazine have had many years publishing experience across both consumer and Business to Business titles. Naidre Werner, Publishing Director of Pet Trade World, said: “Obviously we are delighted to have this level of circulation after only 18 months, but always knew it could be achievable with digital media. Digital magazines have been growing steadily for a number of years whereas everyone has been aware of falling circulations in printed consumer and business to business magazines for a long time. We decided to launch in a purely digital format mainly because the magazine would be available to a much wider international audience without the cost restrictions linked with using a printed magazine.”</p>
<p>She then went onto add: “This also enables us to keep our advertising costs low. In fact it gives us a cost per 1,000 lower than any other magazine in the market&#8230;&#8230;.even though we’re reaching a much larger audience!”</p>
<p>Claire Barks, Editor of Pet Trade World commented: “We may now be the highest circulating publication in the pet trade market but that doesn’t mean we’ll be resting on our laurels. Our aim was always to produce an innovative and informative title packed with up to the minute news and products and we will most certainly continue to do that. Because we have only been around for a relatively short period of time, there are also relationships to strengthen and build within the trade and that can only help improve our magazine product in the coming months.”</p>
<p>Pet Trade World is circulated monthly by personalised email to 32 countries throughout the world. Being a digital magazine allows PTW to use video and audio inserts and have live web and email links throughout &#8211; making it the only publication to offer readers an immediate call to action with any editorial coverage or advertising promotion.</p>
<p>Recent stats show that around half of the readers each month spend 20 minutes or more reading [on average] over 80% of the issue, and that the News and New Product sections are two of the most popular. Pet Trade World is of course the only truly environmentally friendly publication as it doesn’t use paper! Anyone within the pet trade interested in receiving a copy should email <a href="mailto:editor@pettradeworld.com">editor@pettradeworld.com</a> or  go to the ‘Subscribe’ section.</p>
						</div>
																						<p class="postmetadata"><span class="tags"></span></p>
